<br>
But let's actually analyze the time spent per pole.<br>
<br>
The time to get fishing to 200 should not be underestimated though, it IS quite long... I know, I've been trying (I need 175 for Crucibles of Escape).<br>
<br>
If you figure you'll make 50 poles over your fishing career, which seems reasonsable to me, and it took you let's say 10 hours to raise fishing to 200 (this depends on your intelligence... mine's only about 145 in full int gear), then that's about .2 hours or 12 minutes per pole.  When I get essences I do 4 stacks at a time, that's 80 essesnces... but to keep our numbers easy let's say they get 60 and have a few failures.  A run to Ak Annon takes me about 50 minutes, as I can't gate.  Now, I do other things (like look for oxides) along the way, but 50 is nice for this demo.  So that's about 1 minute per pole.<br>
<br>
Getting CoV faction and level 46 is something I think we can assume you'd do anyway, so let's not factor that in.<br>
<br>
Getting to the plain of growth to forage pretty much requires being a druid or ranger.  That's just a supplyer limitation, doesn't take time, just reduces producers.  However it does mean 1 pole every 24 minutes... I'm not sure what the failure rate is so let's just assume perfect success rate here. <br>
<br>
Blessed Emralds are usually done on a per stack basis... when I collect these for Golden Tunare Idols it usually takes me about 20 minutes to find someone to do this (most druids can, and I've paid off a few druids with heavily discounted golden tunare idols, I'll assume the pole maker can do something similar to get a regular crew).  You can do other things while you wait for imbueing, but let's just say it's 30 minutes total per stack to do this, so that's 2.5 stacks of emralds, but the .5 stack will take about as long as a full stack, so that's roughly 90 minutes total, with 50 poles that's .555 minutes per pole.  Running to thurgadin is another 30 minutes, plus let's say 10 minutes to make the spool... that's ignoring the time in Velks to collect the velium, I'm just assuming you'd fight there anyway, it's good enough exp.   We'll assume you make 5 spools per trip (can't fill up the bank too much, one runs out of room) so that's roughly 40 minutes per five spools, or 8 minutes per spool, with one one spool per pole.  I'm not sure on dragon eggs, I believe that's foraged a little more rapidly than poles, so let's say 30 minutes to get to West Wastes (never been but I hear it's tough), forage a stack in two hours (does that seem right?), and do all your foraging in one go.  That's 5 minutes per egg plus 30 minutes to get there, assume you gate back with a gate potion or port spell, if you gate back take the spires to the nexus, that's about 300 minutes total, devided by 50 is 6 minutes per pole.<br>
<br>
Getting tailoring to 150 is a lot of time, let's say 20 hours perhaps?  That seems a pretty conservative guess to me.  Brewing and pottery would take about 3 hours to get to those levels.  So that's another 27.6 minutes per pole.<br>
<br>
End result, assuming a ranger is foraging... it's a bit lower for druids who can avoid the spires... is 79.15555 minutes spent per pole produced.  Now, I rounded a bit but I did it in both directions.<br>
<br>
I dunno, that's a lot of time to make one stinkin' pole.<br>
<br>
I'm not a seller of these things, though... can anyone else check my numbers?<br>
