<br>
When you want to trade skill to make a living then everything else is a distraction and time sink.  Levelling?  Gets in the way.  Gathering components?  That's time invested.  If you have to get to 46 to forage planar oak then you factor that time into the cost of planar oak.  If you're going to get to 46 anyway then you don't.<br>
<br>
The basic analogies differ.  <br>
<br>
One group says that once you reach a certain point of skill making an item is easy and you shoul charge based on cost.<br>
<br>
The other is that of the doctor or the plumber.  You invest a lot of time to be capable of making high end tradeskill items.  You expect to charge to pay yourself for that entire time when you reach the point you can finally make the items.<br>
<br>
Really, criticizing the community only masks the main concern.  That the game has been designed with tradeskills as a sideline NOT something you can effectively make the focus of your character's life.<br>
<br>
Perhaps EQ2 will fix that.  Perhaps not.  Until then, sadly, making tradeskilling your character's primary function is ineffective (at least on FV where there are no alts).  It's a pity though, I think more RPing would come from having merchant class PCs hanging around than forcing everyone into adventuring mode. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/utrallosdrachen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Trallos Drachen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 54<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/14/02 11:33:41 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm49.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=16.topic&index=55>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: You want it? You got it punk!</span><hr size=1> As off topic as this post has wandered lets get it back on track.<br>
